item.title: Rip rswebcliets
item.dc:creator: @Kidpaparoach Kidpaparoach
item.description:
@Kidpaparoach wrote:

[quote=“Trisidia, post:20, topic:528026”][quote author=Kidpaparoach link=topic=646774.msg4349892#msg4349892 date=1376483383]
^How does only caring about money make you a retard? I would take down the site if it wasn’t profiting for me too, if anything he’s being nice; I’d sell the domain and files for a few extra $.

If anything you should respect the guy because he probably realized the site sucked but he still stuck by it (for the money) despite it wrecking what little rep he had.

If I can recall correctly I did hear bad things about the owner so he probably is a bit of a twat but, just calling him an idiot because he did it for the money is very naive regardless.
[/quote]
Your the only one that sticks with him, gf.[/quote]
I guess I am sticking up for him to an extent. I do think rswebclients was a bad site but I don’t think that fact alone makes the owner an ‘idiot’.
People may think he is an ‘idiot’ but that is for multiple reasons and they may be misjudging him because they don’t know the full story which I tried to explain as personally, I will allow myself to look like an idiot etc if it benefits me or the situation I’m in; many other people do things like that too (their are many examples of this, a common one is people play dumb so they don’t have to do something) and I basically said he probably did that which is in fact a smart move.

I’m not calling him smart nor dumb, I’m just pointing out things that you clearly haven’t thought of before stating your opinion on the matter which has completely changed in contract to the OP.

item.title: Rip rswebcliets
item.dc:creator: @system system
item.description:
@system wrote:

iKeptAdvertisingThisSiteSoNowItsCensored, you used RSW? rofl.

EDIT:

pastebin.com

http://pastebin.com/raw/Fdcc7CTN

RSWebclients has been shutdown due to the inability of the staff, I have always said once the site can no longer run itself (money/management or staff), it would be shut down, Well that day has come.

Before anyone asks, the site will never be sold and all domains will remain in my properly. In the future if i see fit, the files for the site may be released along with unprotected loaders for others to use.


I have had a fun time with RSWebclients and it will be a shame to see it go, I hope you enjoyed it as much as i did.

~Kieran
RSWebclients Founder & Creator
